Okay, maybe not.

00:06:46.706 --> 00:06:48.908
The people of Swat Valley.

00:06:48.908 --> 00:06:51.077
When the Talib first came,

00:06:52.211 --> 00:06:55.047 align:start size:84% position:16%
they thought they're
bringing order.

00:06:56.115 --> 00:06:58.551
They're bringing services.

00:06:58.551 --> 00:07:01.821
They established a
court that was faster

00:07:02.789 --> 00:07:05.958 align:start size:84% position:16%
than Pakistani courts.
- Yeah.

00:07:05.958 --> 00:07:08.227
- And the people responded.

00:07:10.329 --> 00:07:12.665
When did that begin to turn?

00:07:14.066 --> 00:07:16.369 align:start size:97% position:3%
- When the Taliban came,
they were trying to convince

00:07:16.369 --> 00:07:19.138
people, and they were just
misusing the name of Islam,

00:07:19.138 --> 00:07:21.674 align:start size:97% position:3%
and they were telling
people, "We will just set up

00:07:21.674 --> 00:07:23.976
"another court for you,
and we will provide you

00:07:23.976 --> 00:07:26.646 align:start size:94% position:6%
"justice on time;"
because usually, in courts

00:07:26.646 --> 00:07:30.783 align:start size:84% position:16%
in Pakistan, people
dies and their case is

00:07:30.783 --> 00:07:34.220
not yet resolving in the courts.

00:07:34.220 --> 00:07:36.956
So that's what is happening
in the courts of Pakistan.

00:07:36.956 --> 00:07:40.259 align:start size:97% position:3%
So people just said like,
"If the Taliban are doing it,

00:07:40.259 --> 00:07:41.994
"why don't we support them?"

00:07:41.994 --> 00:07:45.198
But then they were
that much crueler.

00:07:45.198 --> 00:07:47.300 align:start size:84% position:16%
They started
slaughtering people,

00:07:47.300 --> 00:07:51.804
and they even blasted a
generator of electricity

00:07:51.804 --> 00:07:54.507 align:start position:0%
and it was the month of
Ramadan, in which we keep fast,

00:07:54.507 --> 00:07:55.975
in which we don't
eat on the day,

00:07:55.975 --> 00:07:59.011 align:start size:88% position:13%
in which we don't drink
for the whole day.

00:07:59.011 --> 00:08:01.380 align:start size:88% position:13%
They blasted the
electricity generators,

00:08:01.380 --> 00:08:02.782
which was providing electricity

00:08:02.782 --> 00:08:05.384
to the whole city of Mingora;

00:08:05.384 --> 00:08:07.854
and we could not have
water because it is,

00:08:07.854 --> 00:08:10.890 align:start size:88% position:13%
electricity's related
to water supply as well.

00:08:10.890 --> 00:08:13.826 align:start size:84% position:16%
And people were
sitting in the dark,

00:08:13.826 --> 00:08:16.362
people could not buy
electricity generators,

00:08:16.362 --> 00:08:19.398
people were just sitting
in the light of candles,

00:08:19.398 --> 00:08:22.568 align:start size:94% position:6%
and people were just dying
of thirst at that time.

00:08:22.568 --> 00:08:24.170
But my father is a great father,

00:08:24.170 --> 00:08:27.006 align:start size:88% position:13%
because he bought
generator for the school

00:08:27.006 --> 00:08:29.642
to create electricity and

00:08:29.642 --> 00:08:32.345
to provide water to the street

00:08:32.345 --> 00:08:35.014
and to that community, but still

00:08:35.014 --> 00:08:37.416
many people were suffering from

00:08:37.416 --> 00:08:40.520
that hard situation;
and other than that,

00:08:40.520 --> 00:08:42.855 align:start size:97% position:3%
our freedom was taken from us.
- [Jon] Yes.

00:08:42.855 --> 00:08:44.323
- The women's freedom.

00:08:44.323 --> 00:08:46.058
We could not go to market,

00:08:46.058 --> 00:08:48.694
we were not allowed
to go to school,

00:08:48.694 --> 00:08:50.997
we were just kept imprisoned.

00:08:50.997 --> 00:08:54.634
We were just limited to the
four walls of our house.

00:08:54.634 --> 00:08:56.769
Women's rights were
denied at that time,

00:08:56.769 --> 00:08:58.304
and that's why I spoke.

00:08:58.304 --> 00:08:59.772
Because I believe in equality,

00:08:59.772 --> 00:09:01.641 align:start size:84% position:16%
and I believe that
there is no difference

00:09:01.641 --> 00:09:03.576
between a man and a woman.

00:09:03.576 --> 00:09:06.712
I even believe that a woman
is more powerful than men.

00:09:06.712 --> 00:09:07.980
- What, wait! Whoa!
(women cheering)

00:09:07.980 --> 00:09:09.815
Wait, what? What?
(Malala laughing)

00:09:09.815 --> 00:09:10.650
I-- wait!

00:09:14.520 --> 00:09:18.457 align:start size:84% position:16%
(whistling)
You know, Malala...

00:09:19.792 --> 00:09:23.896 align:start size:88% position:13%
This was going so well.
(laughter)

00:09:23.896 --> 00:09:26.399
You were doing so beautifully,

00:09:27.833 --> 00:09:29.769
and then suddenly, bam!

00:09:32.004 --> 00:09:34.840
This is the part that they,

00:09:34.840 --> 00:09:37.944
they began to say,
"You cannot dance.

00:09:39.946 --> 00:09:42.081 align:start size:72% position:28%
- Yeah.
- "You cannot,

00:09:42.081 --> 00:09:44.317
"the women cannot
do these things."

00:09:44.317 --> 00:09:48.054 align:start size:88% position:13%
You say that many people
believe this is a...

00:09:49.555 --> 00:09:53.225
wrong interpretation
of Islam, of the Koran.

00:09:56.429 --> 00:09:58.898
Why have the Taliban,

00:09:58.898 --> 00:10:00.733
and these more extreme groups,

00:10:00.733 --> 00:10:03.336
been able to be successful?

00:10:03.336 --> 00:10:07.173 align:start size:88% position:13%
Is it the fear that they
bring to these towns?

00:10:08.874 --> 00:10:13.045
Is that why the people have had
a hard time throwing it off?

00:10:14.480 --> 00:10:16.716 align:start size:94% position:6%
- The first thing is that,
they were really cruel.

00:10:16.716 --> 00:10:19.619 align:start size:97% position:3%
They had Kalashnikovs, they
had guns in their hand.

00:10:19.619 --> 00:10:20.886
And if I have a gun in my hand,

00:10:20.886 --> 00:10:22.688 align:start size:84% position:16%
and I tell you
something, 'do this,'

00:10:22.688 --> 00:10:26.325 align:start size:97% position:3%
you have to do that,
because it's for your life.

00:10:26.325 --> 00:10:28.027
So there was fear all around.

00:10:28.027 --> 00:10:30.529 align:start size:88% position:13%
That's why people
could not say anything.

00:10:30.529 --> 00:10:32.331
Then the second thing
was that they were

00:10:32.331 --> 00:10:34.033
misusing the name of Islam.

00:10:34.033 --> 00:10:35.001
They were telling people that

00:10:35.001 --> 00:10:36.268
"We are doing this for Islam,

00:10:36.268 --> 00:10:37.737
"we are doing this for Allah,

00:10:37.737 --> 00:10:40.006 align:start size:97% position:3%
"we are doing this for
Prophet, peace be upon him."

00:10:40.006 --> 00:10:41.774
So essentially, they
were using religion

00:10:41.774 --> 00:10:43.743
for their own personal benefit.

00:10:43.743 --> 00:10:45.711
That's also the reason.

00:10:45.711 --> 00:10:49.715
But then later on, people
tried to realize this,

00:10:49.715 --> 00:10:51.951
and the girls are very brave.

00:10:51.951 --> 00:10:53.719 align:start size:84% position:16%
And girls in our
school, like we were

00:10:53.719 --> 00:10:56.022 align:start size:88% position:13%
at that time, we were
just 11 or 12 years old.

00:10:56.022 --> 00:10:58.658 align:start size:97% position:3%
But we spoke up for our
rights to every media channel,

00:10:58.658 --> 00:11:00.893 align:start size:81% position:19%
to every newspaper
that we could.

00:11:00.893 --> 00:11:03.596
And we did not know at that
time that our small interview

00:11:03.596 --> 00:11:06.065
would have an impact
or not, but it had.

00:11:06.065 --> 00:11:08.467 align:start size:84% position:16%
Because we were
raising up our voice

00:11:08.467 --> 00:11:10.302
and we were speaking
up for our rights.

00:11:10.302 --> 00:11:12.038
And we were speaking
for peace in Swat.

00:11:12.038 --> 00:11:13.773
We wanted to live a normal life,

00:11:13.773 --> 00:11:16.409
because Swat is like
a paradise on Earth.

00:11:16.409 --> 00:11:19.311
I believe in two paradises:

00:11:19.311 --> 00:11:21.047
one I'll get after death,

00:11:21.047 --> 00:11:23.115
but the other one
that is on Earth,

00:11:23.115 --> 00:11:24.350
for me, that is Swat,

00:11:24.350 --> 00:11:26.318
because Swat is
really beautiful,

00:11:26.318 --> 00:11:28.788 align:start size:88% position:13%
and you would be
astonished when you see

00:11:28.788 --> 00:11:30.356 align:start size:84% position:16%
the lush green hills,
and when you see

00:11:30.356 --> 00:11:33.492
the tall mountains, and
the rivers that we have,

00:11:33.492 --> 00:11:36.796
the crystal-clear water,
and you can find trout,

00:11:36.796 --> 00:11:39.465 align:start size:94% position:6%
so it's really beautiful:
you'll love Swat.

00:11:39.465 --> 00:11:41.600
- Malala, I'm from New Jersey.

00:11:41.600 --> 00:11:45.471 align:start size:88% position:13%
(laughter and cheering)
So...

00:11:45.471 --> 00:11:47.540 align:start size:94% position:6%
I know a little
something about paradise.

00:11:47.540 --> 00:11:50.576
(laughter)
The beaches--

00:11:50.576 --> 00:11:53.245 align:start size:84% position:16%
It does, it sounds
magnificent, and it's,

00:11:53.245 --> 00:11:57.383
it is heartbreaking,
because you see what

00:11:57.383 --> 00:11:59.919
these children want, and
what these people want,

00:11:59.919 --> 00:12:01.854
is to just live in peace

00:12:03.389 --> 00:12:06.358
without having this
imposed on them.

00:12:06.358 --> 00:12:08.294 align:start size:75% position:25%
- Yeah.
- And I think--

00:12:09.662 --> 00:12:12.732 align:start size:81% position:19%
We don't know what
to do to help.

00:12:12.732 --> 00:12:15.367
You know, there are
passages in the book

00:12:15.367 --> 00:12:18.137
about the United States.

00:12:18.137 --> 00:12:22.508 align:start size:84% position:16%
And we come out great.
(laughter)

00:12:22.508 --> 00:12:25.111
But there is, there are attacks

00:12:26.278 --> 00:12:29.682
in Swat and in those
areas with drones,

00:12:29.682 --> 00:12:32.952
and they talk about
a man, a CIA agent,

00:12:34.820 --> 00:12:37.189
who shot two men in Lahore.

00:12:37.189 --> 00:12:38.624
Raymond--
- Davis.

00:12:41.327 --> 00:12:42.495
- And this is,

00:12:43.829 --> 00:12:46.799
I think we have a common want

00:12:46.799 --> 00:12:48.734
and desire, but perhaps

00:12:49.802 --> 00:12:51.904
are not accomplishing it

00:12:51.904 --> 00:12:55.074
in the manner that
shows the people...

00:12:56.642 --> 00:12:59.011
how we feel; but in some ways,

00:12:59.011 --> 00:13:01.447
we don't know what else to do.

00:13:02.848 --> 00:13:06.051
What is your thought on that?

00:13:06.051 --> 00:13:10.623
- I think that the people of
America, the United States,

00:13:10.623 --> 00:13:14.326 align:start size:88% position:13%
they truly support
peace, and they say that

00:13:14.326 --> 00:13:17.096 align:start size:94% position:6%
"We must not fight
against war through war."

00:13:17.096 --> 00:13:19.498 align:start size:94% position:6%
They believe that
dialogue is the best way.

00:13:19.498 --> 00:13:21.901 align:start size:88% position:13%
And we must try to
find a solution for it.

00:13:21.901 --> 00:13:25.571
And in my opinion, the
solution that would work

00:13:25.571 --> 00:13:27.740
to fight all these wars
and all these problems

00:13:27.740 --> 00:13:30.943 align:start size:88% position:13%
that people are facing,
is only education.

00:13:30.943 --> 00:13:33.145
Because you can--

00:13:33.145 --> 00:13:34.647
you can stop war for a second,

00:13:34.647 --> 00:13:37.550 align:start size:94% position:6%
but you don't know it
would start again or not.

00:13:37.550 --> 00:13:38.684
We have seen First World War,

00:13:38.684 --> 00:13:40.019
we have seen Second World War,

00:13:40.019 --> 00:13:41.987 align:start size:84% position:16%
and I think Third
World War is coming;

00:13:41.987 --> 00:13:45.524
but I believe that
we must stop it now.

00:13:45.524 --> 00:13:49.895 align:start size:97% position:3%
I don't want to see a Third
World War in this world again.

00:13:49.895 --> 00:13:52.164 align:start size:97% position:3%
And the best way to fight
against this war is education

00:13:52.164 --> 00:13:55.868 align:start size:94% position:6%
because, as we can see,
the children are suffering

00:13:55.868 --> 00:13:58.370
from terrorism, they are
suffering from child labor

00:13:58.370 --> 00:13:59.605
and child trafficking.

00:13:59.605 --> 00:14:01.273
They are also suffering from

00:14:01.273 --> 00:14:02.842 align:start size:81% position:19%
the cultural norms
and tradition.

00:14:02.842 --> 00:14:04.510
These are, there is
not only one issue

00:14:04.510 --> 00:14:05.945
that we are facing through.

00:14:05.945 --> 00:14:07.980
There are many others as well.

00:14:07.980 --> 00:14:10.716 align:start size:84% position:16%
So I think education
is the best way.

00:14:10.716 --> 00:14:12.651 align:start size:88% position:13%
People will be thinking,
just going to school,

00:14:12.651 --> 00:14:14.620
learning about chemistry,
and physics, and maths,

00:14:14.620 --> 00:14:16.455
and that's it.

00:14:16.455 --> 00:14:18.490 align:start size:84% position:16%
Going to school is not
only learning about

00:14:18.490 --> 00:14:21.227 align:start size:94% position:6%
different subjects: it
teaches you communication,

00:14:21.227 --> 00:14:23.796 align:start size:94% position:6%
it teaches you how to live
a life, it teaches you

00:14:23.796 --> 00:14:26.999
about history, it teaches you
about how science is working.

00:14:26.999 --> 00:14:29.869 align:start size:88% position:13%
And other than that, you
learn about equality;

00:14:29.869 --> 00:14:32.571 align:start size:94% position:6%
because students are
provided the same benches,

00:14:32.571 --> 00:14:35.274
they sit equally, it
shows us equality,

00:14:35.274 --> 00:14:39.011
it teaches students how to
live with others together,

00:14:39.011 --> 00:14:40.746
how to accept each
other's language,

00:14:40.746 --> 00:14:42.448
how to accept each
other's traditions

00:14:42.448 --> 00:14:44.250
and each other's religion.

00:14:44.250 --> 00:14:46.118
It also teaches us justice.

00:14:46.118 --> 00:14:48.888
It also teaches us respect.

00:14:48.888 --> 00:14:50.789
It teaches us how
to live together.

00:14:50.789 --> 00:14:52.958
So that's why I support the,

00:14:52.958 --> 00:14:56.095 align:start size:97% position:3%
I support the idea of
sending children to school,

00:14:56.095 --> 00:14:58.664
because it is the best
way to fight terrorism.

00:14:58.664 --> 00:15:01.734 align:start size:94% position:6%
And I want people to
support us in this cause,

00:15:01.734 --> 00:15:03.502 align:start size:97% position:3%
and through Malala
Foundation, we want to work

00:15:03.502 --> 00:15:07.106
for education of girls in
the developing countries,

00:15:07.106 --> 00:15:08.540
especially in Syria now.

00:15:08.540 --> 00:15:10.442 align:start size:84% position:16%
They are suffering,
they are homeless now.

00:15:10.442 --> 00:15:12.211 align:start size:88% position:13%
We want to help
children in Afghanistan,

00:15:12.211 --> 00:15:15.915 align:start position:0%
because they have been suffering
from terrorism for decades.

00:15:15.915 --> 00:15:17.850 align:start size:94% position:6%
We want to help the
children of India as well,

00:15:17.850 --> 00:15:20.052 align:start size:88% position:13%
because they are
victims of child labor.

00:15:20.052 --> 00:15:22.321
So I think issues and
problems are enormous;

00:15:22.321 --> 00:15:24.757
but solution is one,
and that is simple.

00:15:24.757 --> 00:15:26.926
That is education.

